Brett Tabisel https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Brett_Tabisel 0 Brett Tabisel (born September 14, 1982) is an American actor. He performed in Big: the musical in 1996, he won an award, and was nominated for two awards. He played roles in the films Strong Island Boys, Returning Mickey Stern, Dirty Deeds, and Frat Brothers of the KVL. He has made guest appearances in the television series Law Order: Special Victims Unit, Chappelle's Show, Ed, and the web series Red Oaks. He also has provided voices in video games by Rockstar Games such as Bully as the nerd character Algernon "Algie" Papadopoulos, as well as additional local population voices in Grand Theft Auto V.
